id: pm-ukml
title: "GH-596: update-many --ids must report nonexistent requested IDs"
description: "Bulk explicit-ID mutations silently omit nonexistent IDs while reporting a fully successful matched subset, so agents cannot distinguish a complete request from a partial one."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[5]: agent-ux,"area:cli",bulk-ops,data-integrity,gh-issue
created_at: "2026-07-18T15:09:38.855Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-18T15:09:38.855Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: update-many reports unmatched_ids and unmatched_count for explicit --ids; dry-run and apply envelopes agree; existing matched rows remain deterministic; CLI and contract tests cover mixed valid/missing IDs; GH-596 is resolved
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: low
confidence: high
dependencies[2]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-1h99,related,"2026-07-18T15:09:38.855Z",null,null
  pm-j2ig,related,"2026-07-18T15:09:38.855Z",null,null
body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/596\n\nThe 2026.7.18 CLI exits 0 for --ids containing valid and nonexistent IDs, but exposes only the matched subset and zero failures. Preserve partial-success behavior if desired, but make omission machine-detectable without client-side set differencing. Duplicate check searched all statuses for update-many, explicit IDs, nonexistent/missing/unmatched IDs. Closed pm-1h99 introduced --ids and explicitly documented that nonexistent IDs disappear; no item tracks surfacing that loss."
